COGmapper
version 0.1

Yu-Wei Wu (yuwei.wu@tmu.edu.tw)
Graduate Institute of Biomedical Informatics, Taipei Medical University

[Introduction]
This script is used to get COG (Clusters of Orthologous Groups)  category distributions for a set of prokaryotic genomes

[Prerequisite]
This script needs the following additional software
  - HMMER3
  - Prodigal
  - COG files downloaded from eggNOG website (please refer to the tutorial file for this step)

[Usage]
  perl map_COG.pl (list file) (output file)

[Example]
Several example genome files are placed at "test_genomes" folder. A list file is also included.
To run the map_COG script please do as follows:
cd (COGmapper folder)/test_genomes
perl (COGmapper folder)/map_COG.pl list out



